==English==

===Etymology===
From [[jade]], a worn-out horse, possibly from Old Norse [[jalda]] "mare". As a term of abuse for a woman, it dates from 1560. [http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?search=jaded&searchmode=none]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/dʒeɪdɛd/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Worn out, [[wearied]], or lacking [[enthusiasm]]; [[exhausted]].
# Cynically [[insensitive]]; made [[callous]] by experience.

